Thank you for providing the log file information. It seems that the error is occurring because `selectedThumbnails` is not being recognized as an array, which is why the `map` function is not available.

In Adobe Bridge, the `getSelection()` method actually returns a `Thumbnail` object or a `Thumbnail` array, depending on the number of items selected. When only one item is selected, instead of an array with one element, Bridge gives you a single `Thumbnail` object, which does not have a `map` function. This might be the reason behind the error message you're seeing.

Let's correct this behavior by ensuring `selectedThumbnails` is always treated as an array, regardless of the number of items selected:

```javascript
#target bridge
if (BridgeTalk.appName == "bridge") {
    var logFile = new File(Folder.desktop + "/bridgeScriptLog.txt");

    var copyFilenamesMenu = MenuElement.create('command', 'Copy Filenames to Clipboard', 'at the end of tools');

    copyFilenamesMenu.onSelect = function() {
        log('Menu item selected. Processing...');

        try {
            // Get the selected thumbnails
            var selection = app.document.getSelection();
            // Ensure selection is always an array
            var selectedThumbnails = selection instanceof Array ? selection : [selection];
            log('Retrieved ' + selectedThumbnails.length + ' selected thumbnails.');

            // Extract filenames from the thumbnails
            var filenames = selectedThumbnails.map(function(thumbnail) {
                return decodeURI(thumbnail.name); // decodeURI just in case there are escaped characters
            });
            log('Mapped ' + filenames.length + ' filenames.');

            // Join the filenames into a single string with line breaks
            var namesString = filenames.join("\r\n");
            log('Joined filenames into a single string.');

            // Attempt to set text to clipboard
            app.setClipboard(namesString);
            log('Attempted to set clipboard data.');

            // Show an alert to indicate the success of the operation
            alert("Copied " + selectedThumbnails.length + " filenames to the clipboard.");
        } catch (error) {
            log('An error occurred: ' + error.description);
            alert('Failed to copy filenames. Please check the log file on your Desktop for details.');
        }
    };

    function log(message) {
        logFile.open('a');
        logFile.writeln(new Date() + ': ' + message);
        logFile.close();
    }

    logFile.open('w');
    logFile.writeln('Bridge Script Log Started');
    logFile.close();

    log('Startup script loaded successfully.');
}
```

The modification made is to check if the `selection` is an instance of Array. If not, it will create an array containing that single selection. This should resolve the error because the `map` function is now always called on an array.

